main event: A round, continuous blue-and-white object was observed in the sky over Naperville, Illinois on March 17, 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed for 4 minutes.
The observation was made by a civilian.
The report states that there was insufficient data available for further analysis.
The report was submitted to the Air Force Systems Command, Foreign Technology Division at Wright-Patterson AFB.
The report was submitted by the Base Operations Officer, Thomas A. Hillquist.
